args: (This must be a dream. There's a\nyounger me, and he's crying, after all.)
(Serious, studious Lady Mitsuhide changed\novernight into a layabout. I was so torn up\nabout it that I cried until I couldn't see.)
Lady Mitsuhide! I...*sob* I don't WANT\nyou to be a different person!
Is it because you're an adult now?\nBecause you ＂grew up＂?
Is that gonna happen to me someday?\nThat makes me so sad. My heart hurts...
Morning, sunshine. You've been asleep\nfor nearly three days.
Three days?! I must have been such a\nburden on you.
You sure were. And you know what\ncaused it all? You not knowing when\nto cool your jets.
What were you thinking? You could have\ndied from this, you know. Tell me that's\nnot what you wanted, Chitose.
I wasn't TRYING to die. But if the\nalternative is becoming an adult...\nThen yeah, I think I'd rather die.
You don't want to become an adult? Why?
Because it means giving up my cuteness.
For a while now, I've seen ＂growing up＂\nas synonymous with ＂losing something.＂
I think the first time it crossed my mind\nwas when you entered into your soulpact.

In part, yes. And also because since the
moment you made your soulpact, you've
changed. You were once such a hard
worker, but you've done a total 180.
It's as though something is missing.\nIt made me wonder if that's what\n＂becoming an adult＂ means.
Hold up, pal. You're being a tad mawkish.\nI don't think I lost anything when I made\nmy pact.

Making the pact AND deciding to chill
out were both what I wanted. Frankly,
I'm upset that you came to that conclusion
without even asking me.
Lemme just say this: becoming an adult\ndoesn't mean letting go of who you are.
But I thought that cuteness and adulthood\ncouldn't mix!
Y'know, I dunno why you're so self-assured\nabout the whole ＂cuteness＂ thing.
Hey! Why would you say that?! Even if\nyou won't acknowledge it, *I* know I'm\npositively adorable!
Then what are you so worked up for? Just\nkeep knowing you're cute no matter how\nold you get.
What got you so hung up on the idea that\nyou'd suddenly lose that upon growing up?
Erm, well... I mean... Uh, now that you\nmention it, why DID I think that?
That's literally what I just asked you!\n*sigh* It's all good. Let's just give it a\nrest for today. See ya.
So I DON'T have to lose something upon\nbecoming an adult, huh?
I feel foolish for not getting it until now.\nI don't need anyone else's validation to\nfeel cute. Only I can decide that.
From this day on, whatever trials await\nme, I shall burst through them with my\ninnate charisma! Cuteness! Is! Justice!
Several weeks later, on the day of\nChitose's coming-of-age exam...
I see. Judging by your outfit, I take it to\nmean that you've given up on becoming\nan adult.
You mustn't judge a book by its cover,\nFather—even if that book is bedazzled\nto the moon and back!
I can't argue that I'm decked out from\nhead to toe in adorable accoutrements.\nI am cuteness made manifest, after all!

Father, I've been thinking. Just because
I'm becoming an adult doesn't mean I
need to abandon who I am. Nor do I
have to become big and burly.
But you know what? I WANT to become a\n＂strong, stout man＂—just with a cute twist!

So look at me, as I am now. I'm going to
conquer my coming-of-age exam as my
true self! Watch, and see how strong my
resolve really is!
I see. Then as a parent, it falls to me\nto bring you back down to reality.
I will harden my heart and give you a\ncoming-of-age exam you'll not soon forget!

Defeat all of these opponents. Should you
emerge victorious, I will acknowledge that
you have come of age—as the strong,
stout, and cute man you claim to be.
Now we're talking! Get ready to eat the\ncutest crow you've ever had, Father!
Surely you realize the error of your ways\nby now, my son.
No! You don't get to decide who\nI am and what I can or can't do!\nI will be CUTE, and I will succeed!
You would still proclaim ＂cuteness,＂\nfilthy and ragged as you are?!
I would! Even if I were to roll in the mud,\nit wouldn't matter, because my cuteness\ncomes from within!

And so long as I believe in myself,
then I'll always, forever, and eternally
be the cutest little button under the sun!
HIIIYAAAH!
Cuteness is embedded in my very spirit!\nYou were fools to doubt my resolve!
And so, I defeated every last challenger\nwith the almighty power of cuteness.
My father was convinced, my problems\nwere resolved, and I found an indelible\nsense of pride in being true to myself.
You have to be making this up.\nYou HAVE to.
I'm serious as a heart attack! But, like,\na cute little heart, not a gross, veiny one.
Hmmm... You know, I think I kind of get it.
You really thought long and hard about\nwhat cuteness means to you.
See, she gets it! You've been following\nalong much better than Vice, haven't you?
Oh, can it. I use facts and logic. A pro like\nme can't act on feelings and emotions.
You're good at what you do, Vice, but I\nthink Chitose is a pro in his own way, too!
Yeah! That's why next time I'm in trouble,\nI'm going to ask Chitose to help again!
I'll be like, ＂Please, Chitose, save me with\nthe almighty power of cuteness!＂

And I will swoop into action, of course!
Whatever woes you might have, by my
honor as a bona fide cutie, I'll have them
solved with a wink and a sparkle!
